swingtree.api.mvvm

Interface ViewableEntry

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Viewable

    public interface ViewableEntry
extends Viewable
    A ViewableEntry is used to model an entry inside of the JScrollPanels component. It is expected to be a view model with 2 default properties:
    - isSelected()
    - position()
    The isSelected() method defines a boolean property determining whether the entry is currently selected or not.
    The position() method defines an integer property determining the position of the entry in the list of all entries.

    Note that implementations of this are not supposed to be part of your UI code. They are supposed to be part of your business logic code in the form of view models.
